(556,'\0','Emma Thomas (born 9 December 1971) is a British film producer, known for co-producing films such as The Prestige (2006), Inception (2010), The Dark Knight Trilogy (2005–2012), Interstellar (2014), Dunkirk (2017) and Tenet (2020). She frequently collaborates with her husband, filmmaker Christopher Nolan.','1971-12-09',1,NULL,'nm0858799','Production','Emma Thomas','London, England, UK',4.559,'/6GemtNCy856iLho6WRsFASxQTAp.jpg'),
(557,'\0','From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia\n\nColleen Atwood (born September 25, 1948) is an American costume designer.\n\nAtwood has been nominated for the Academy Award for Best Costume Design twelve times, winning four times - for the films Chicago (2002), Memoirs of a Geisha (2005), Alice in Wonderland (2010), and Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them (2016); the latter is the first Wizarding World film to win an Academy Award. She has collaborated several times with directors Tim Burton, Rob Marshall and Jonathan Demme.','1948-11-25',1,NULL,'nm0041181','Costume & Make-Up','Colleen Atwood','Yakima, Washington, USA',2.134,'/c0YNyYEoeFyp3VX1asPThzcpz9w.jpg'),
