(1697,'\0','Takeshi Seyama (born 1944) is a Japanese film editor from Tokyo.\n\nSeyama is the editor of many anime series and movies from Studio Ghibli, Katsuhiro Otomo, and Satoshi Kon, including hits such as Princess Mononoke, Steamboy, and Paprika. In 1992, Seyama founded the \"Seyama Editing Room,\" which specializes in editing anime.','1944-01-01',2,NULL,'nm0786707','Editing','Takeshi Seyama','Tokyo, Japan',1.637,'/2ZoMQKCyNiUCYo8sy6pDIb30ViV.jpg'),
