(8559,'\0','Kátia Lund (born 1966 in São Paulo) is an American-Brazilian film director and screenwriter. Her most notable work was as co-director of the film City of God.\n\nLund\'s parents are Americans who emigrated to Brazil before she was born. She graduated from Escola Maria Imaculada, an American Catholic school in São Paulo where she excelled in art. She then attended Brown University where she became interested in filmmaking.\n\nFrom Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia','1966-01-01',1,'http://www.katialund.com/','nm0526199','Directing','Kátia Lund','São Paulo, São Paulo, Brazil',1.985,'/8jNK0JjXe6e47G9VgBtGutLadKK.jpg'),
